    "html": "<h2>The problem worth solving</h2>\n<p>Enterprise clients across multiple industries needed to unify sales, service and field operations on a single, governed SAP foundation — re-platforming legacy CRM and service systems onto SAP's V2 CX stack without recreating the integration debt that had made the old estate brittle.</p>\n<h2>What was built</h2>\n<p>Leading the CX practice's architecture, Venkata delivered end-to-end implementations spanning <strong>lead-to-cash, service-to-cash and field-to-finish</strong>. Sales Cloud V2 was configured for advanced opportunity management, guided selling and approval orchestration integrated with SAP CPQ and S/4HANA pricing. Service Cloud V2 handled omnichannel ticketing, SLA tracking and IoT-based service triggers wired into FSM and S/4 service orders. FSM covered dispatching, resource planning and mobile technician execution with offline closure.</p>\n<p>At the centre sat a <strong>BTP/CPI integration hub</strong> governing master-data replication, transactional synchronisation and event-driven APIs between the CX clouds and S/4HANA — with custom iFlows for real-time updates of business partners, service contracts and installed-base objects. AI-assisted analytics and predictive routing used SAP Joule and SAC Predictive Insights to sharpen lead conversion and SLA adherence.</p>\n<h2>The outcome</h2>\n<p>A fully integrated CX + S/4 architecture that reduced <strong>quote-to-order cycle time by 35%</strong> and <strong>service-order processing by 40%</strong>, enabled predictive dispatching that lifted <strong>first-time-fix by 28%</strong>, and achieved seamless real-time synchronisation of <strong>500k+ master records</strong> over BTP CPI. The reusable CX Integration Blueprint from this work became a standard for subsequent V2 deployments.</p>\n<h2>Why it matters</h2>\n<p>This is the three layers as one design problem — platform, cognition and human on a single governed architecture — with the numbers to show it lands.</p>",
